subSubSection.paragraph:
Diagnosis.
Thorax green (female and sexually immature male) or pruinose blue (mature male), dorsum of abdomen green with narrow stripes black on lateral, transversal and dorsal carinae on S2-9, stripes wider in S7-9 (female and sexually immature male), or pruinose blue (mature male). Abdominal appendages black. Basal area hyaline. Posterior extension of ventral teeth on male cercus beyond level of apex of epiproct (
Fig. 12
). Posterior lobe of vesica spermalis absent, lateral lobe extended more posteriorly than medial lobe. Hook bilobed and not perpendicular to the longitudinal axis of vesica spermalis (
Fig. 18
). Cornua parallel to vesica spermalis transversal axis, with lobes fused to apex, and not covered by lateral lobes in lateral view (
Fig. 20
). In ventral view vulvar lamina triangular, not projected to the posterior region and with the posterior border acute. Lab ≤ 
30mm
, LcaS4/LclS4>2.10; WmS2/LcaS5 <3.
